===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*mV-kЙҷm||to put into mouth; to seize with mouth}} (STEDT, under *gam); cognate with {{cog|bo|аҪ аҪӮаҪҳајӢаҪ”||to put into the mouth}}, {{cog|sit-tan-pro|*g(j)am||bite}}.

Within Chinese, cognate with {{och-l|еҮҪ|to contain; box; letter}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). {{och-l|йҠң|to carry in the mouth; horse's bit}} is probably related. {{zh-ref|Bodman (1980)}} considers {{och-l|й ·}} to be the [[endoactive]] of {{och-l|еҗ«|to hold in the mouth}}, literally вҖңthe thing that holds something in the mouthвҖқ.

